<h3 style="font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: darkblue; font-style: bold;text-align: center;">Connect Health Server to iOS Files</h3>
<p> </p>
<p id="health_server_ios"> This guide allows you to connect your health server to 'Files' in iOS. This would only be available on local network. iOS seems to use Samba to connect files.  The steps are as follows: </p>

<p>
 1.  Open "Files" on your iOS.
</p> <p>
 2.  Click on "Browse". THis the last tab to the bottom right of the screen. Click "Browse" again until you arrive at "Browse" menu. It will have several options on your screen. 
 </p> <p>
 3.  The subheadings include "Locations", "Favorites", "Shared". When you click on "Shared" it should open a dropdown of connected servers. In your case it might have none that show up.
 </p> <p>
 3. This should also open a settings to the top right in your screen. It is marked by three dots in a cirle. Clicking it should open a dropdown menu saying "Connect to Server".
 </p> <p>
 4. Clicking the option "Connect your server will open an option saying "Server".
 </p> <p> 
 5. Enter your server address that should look something like this: "192.168.99.111:3001".
  </p> <p>
 6. Once you do that it will take you to next page that gives options of "Guest" and "Registered User". Click on "Registered User" and enter you <username> and <password>.
 </p> <p> 
 7. Clicking next will connect you to server.
 </p> <p> 
 8. You should be able to now access your files on local network when you click on "Browse", "Shared" and selecting your server.
  </p> <p>
 
 
 </p>

<h3 style="font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: darkblue; font-style: bold;text-align: center;">Connect Health server to MacOS</h3>
<p id="health_server_macos">
 </p> <p>
 
This guide allows you to connect your health server to MacOS. This would only health server to be available on local network.  The steps are as follows: 
 </p> <p>
1.  To connect your health server on MacOS, press the following keys together : ⌘ + K OR Command + K
 </p> <p>
2.  This will take you to a input bar that says enter you "Server" information.
 </p> <p>
3.  Enter your information that would look something like this: 192.168.99.111:3001. Then press connect.
 </p> <p>
4.  Your mac will now try to connect.
 </p> <p>
5.  To go to your server, click on 'Finder', which is usually the first icon in bottom left of screen.
 </p> <p>
6.  Goto "Locations" and then "Network". Health server should now show up there. On clicking it might prompt you for <username> and <password>.

</p>

<img src="Nextcloud.png">

<h3 style="font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: darkblue; font-style: bold;text-align: center;">Connect NextCloud to Files iOS</h3>
<p id="nextcloud_ios">
 </p> <p>
This guide allows you to connect your Nextcloud to 'Files' in iOS. Downloading the app and configuring your app will allow it to automatically connect to files.  However the steps to access it are as follows if you would still like to access it from "Files":
 </p> <p>
 1.  Open "Files" on your iOS.
 </p> <p>
 2.  Click on "Browse". THis the last tab to the bottom right of the screen. Click "Browse" again until you arrive at "Browse" menu. It will have several options on your screen. 
  </p> <p>
 3.  The subheadings include "Locations", "Favorites", "Shared". "Nextcloud" might show show up in "Locations" if the app is already configured. In this case you are done and could connect by clicking on "Nextcloud".
  </p> <p>
  
 
 
 </p>
 
<h3 style="font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: darkblue; font-style: bold;text-align: center;">Connect Nextcloud to MacOS</h3>
<p id="nextcloud_macos">
This guide allows you to connect your Nextcloud account to MacOS.   The steps are as follows: 
 </p> <p>
1.  To connect your health server on MacOS, press the following keys together : ⌘ + K OR Command + K
 </p> <p>
2.  This will take you to a input bar that says enter you "Server" information.
 </p> <p>
3.  Enter your information that would look something like this: "nextcloud.user.com/remote.php/dav/files/admin". In this please replace <nextcloud.user.com> with your domain address. Then press connect.
 </p> <p>
4.  Your mac will now try to connect.
 </p> <p>
5.  To go to your server, click on 'Finder', which is usually the first icon in bottom left of screen.
 </p> <p>
6.  Goto "Locations" and then "Network". Nextcloud should now show up there. On clicking it might prompt you for <username> and <password>.

</p>


 
